g as parent is non-null. I wonder if I should include tests for public methods too, since all top-level test classes should be public. I might need to inspect dynamic coverage to verify that the class file is absent.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_6BQMPF4bkfh04a5QpWkx71UG|fc_082a49a7d750fe0b0169f2bc3ce048819080a03d233c49a9c2\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"grep -R \\\"class ChildFirstClassLoader\\\" -n tests/src || true && python3 - <<'PY'\\nimport json\\np='tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json'\\ntry:\\n print(open(p).read()[:2000])\\nexcept FileNotFoundError: pass\\nPY\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1209, \"output\": 1410, \"cacheRead\": 11776, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 14395, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777515559488, \"responseId\": \"resp_082a49a7d750fe0b0169f2bc27d49081908c0ebe676d2d24d1\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_6BQMPF4bkfh04a5QpWkx71UG|fc_082a49a7d750fe0b0169f2bc3ce048819080a03d233c49a9c2\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"tests/src/org.immutables/value/2.8.6/src/test/java/org_immutables/value/ProxyProcessorProxyClassLoaderTest.java:87:    private static final class ChildFirstClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\\ntests/src/org.immutables/value/2.8.2/src/test/java/org_immutables/value/ProxyProcessorProxyClassLoaderTest.java:87:    private static final class ChildFirstClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\\ntests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.1.3/src/test/java/ch_qos_logback/logback_core/EnvUtilTest.java:46:    private static final class ChildFirstClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\\ntests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.1.3/src/test/java/ch_qos_logback/logback_core/Loa